ll. The tornado dissipated shortly after.<ref name=\":2\" />\n|-\n|July 25, 2016\n|EF1\n|[[Readington Township, New Jersey|Readington]]-[[Branchburg, New Jersey|Branchburg]], NJ\n|A tornado touched down in Readington Township in Hunterdon County and then moved east towards Somerset County. The tornado (thought at first to be a [[microburst]]) broke several utility poles, threw vehicles up to 100 feet in the air, and downed trees and power lines.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nj.com/somerset/2016/07/branchburg_microburst_throws_cars_100_feet_snaps_p.html|title=Microburst pushes cars 100 feet, snaps poles in Branchburg (PHOTOS)|last=NJ.com|first=Craig Turpin {{!}} NJ Advance Media for|date=2016-07-26|website=nj|language=en|access-date=2019-10-31}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nj.com/weather/2017/06/a_look_at_njs_tornadoes_in_the_past_decade.html|title=How common are tornadoes in N.J.? The answer might surprise you|last=Napoliello|first=Alex|date=2017-06-25|website=nj|language=en|access-date=2019-10-31}}</ref>\n|-\n|July 14, 2016\n|EF0\n|Rocksburg-[[Harmony Township, New Jersey|Harmony]], NJ\n|A tornado touched down near White Township and moved along a path nearly 3 miles long, damaging a barn and a home, and shearing the tops of trees.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nbcnewyork.com/news/local/Tornado-Touchdown-New-Jersey-Warren-County-387048701.html|title=Tornado Touched Down in NJ Thursday: NWS|last=Maxfield|first=Jen|last2=Team 4|first2=Storm|website=NBC New York|language=en|access-date=2019-10-31}}</ref>\n|-\n|October 7, 2013\n|EF1\n|[[Paramus, New Jersey|Paramus]], NJ\n|A tornado touched down near the town of Paramus, moving northeast across Bergen County. The tornado damaged an cemetery and an golf course, and snapped and uprooted trees.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://newyork.cbslocal.com/2013/10/08/officials-tornado-touched-down-near-paramus-during-monday-storms/|title=Officials: Tornado Touched Down Near Paramus During Monday Storms|date=2013-10-08|language