{"title_page": "Krook", "text_new": "'''Krook''' is the surname of:\n\n* [[Caroline Krook]] (born 1944), Swedish bishop in the Church of Sweden\n* [[Christina Krook]] (1742-1806), Finnish educator\n* [[Dorothea Krook-Gilead]] (1920-1989), Israeli literary scholar, a translator, and a professor of English literature\n* [[Karl Krook]] (1887 - 1966), Swedish tug of war competitor\n* [[Kevin Krook]] (born 1958),Canadian former professional ice hockey defenceman\n* [[Margaretha Krook]] (1925 \u20132001), Swedish stage and film actress\n* [[Matt Krook]] (born 1994), American left-handed pitcher\n* [[Max Krook]] (1913 \u2013 1985), American mathematician and astrophysicst\n* [[Stefan Krook]] (born 1950), Swedish sailor\n\n'''De Krook''' refers to:\n* [[De Krook]], the new city library (inaugurated 2017) of the City of Ghent, East-Flanders, Belgium. The name of the library refers to the bent in the river Scheldt where it is situated (see below).\n* [[Waalse Krook]], a part of the historic centre of the City of Ghent on the left bank of the river Scheldt. The area derives its name from the bent in the river which in old Dutch was referred to as \"krook\".\n\n{{disambiguation}}\n[[Category:Surnames]]\n", "text_old": "'''Krook''' is the surname of:\n\n* [[Caroline Krook]] (born 1944), Swedish bishop in the Church of Sweden\n* [[Christina Krook]] (1742-1806), Finnish educator\n* [[Dorothea Krook-Gilead]] (1920-1989), Israeli literary scholar, a translator, and a professor of English literature\n* [[Karl Krook]] (1887 - 1966), Swedish tug of war competitor\n* [[Kevin Krook]] (born 1958),Canadian former professional ice hockey defenceman\n* [[Margaretha Krook]] (1925 \u20132001), Swedish stage and film actress\n* [[Matt Krook]] (born 1994), American left-handed pitcher\n* [[Max Krook]] (1913 \u2013 1985), American mathematician and astrophysicst\n* [[Stefan Krook]] (born 1950), Swedish sailor\n\n'''De Krook''' refers to:\n* [[De Krook]], the new city library (inaugurated 2017) of the City of Ghent, East-Flanders, Belgium. The name of the library refers to the bent in the river Scheldt were it is situated (see below).\n* [[Waalse Krook]], a part of the historic centre of the City of Ghent on the left bank of the river Scheldt. The area derives its name from the bent in the river which in old Dutch was referred to as \"krook\".\n\n{{disambiguation}}\n[[Category:Surnames]]\n", "name_user": "Kaltenmeyer", "label": "safe", "comment": "were -> where", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Krook"}
